06/01/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police arrested 20 people Tuesday (January 5th) for suspected links to the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK).
The arrests were made in simultaneous operations at 22 locations in four provinces -- Mersin, Gaziantep, Hatay and Adiyaman.
(Anadolu news agency, Press TV, Hurriyet - 05/01/10)
